---->Git:-
	Git is a Source Code Management(SCM) Tool.It is also called as Distributed Version Control System(DVCS).
	It is developed by Linus Torvald in 2005.

----> Installing Git on Linux:-
	sudo yum -y install git
		or
	sudo apt-get install git

----> To check the version of git installed:-
	git --version

----> Initialising a Local Git repository:-
	git init [directory_name]
		or
	git init (By default it will initalise the current directory as git repository).
	Note:- Directory is added with .git folder where all configuration file related to repo is available and it tracks
	and manage repository.

---->  To Configure or Add "username and useremail" for repository:-
	1) For a particular repository:-
		git config user.name "Username"
		git config user.email "username@xyz.com"

	2) For adding globally so that every repo should have same configuration for usetname and useremail:-
		git config --global user.name "Username"
		git config --global user.email "username@xyz.com"

----> To check the Configuration of git repo:-
	git config --list

----> To add local repo to central repo:-
	git remote add origin <centralgit url>

----> To check status of git repo:-
	git status

----> To add workspace data into staging area:-
	git add .
		or
	git add [file_name or directory_name]

----> To commit code in git repo:-
	git commit -m "commit message" .
		or
	git commit -m "coomit message" [file_name or directory_name]

----> To check log file or commit details:-
	git log

----> To show particular commit:-
	git show <commit ID>

----> To set branch name for repo:-
	git branch -M [branch_name]

----> To push local repo to centralised repo:-
	git push -u origin [branch_name]

----> To Pull centralised repo to local repo:-
	git pull -u origin [branch_name]

---->
